body: "Three predicates in src/cli/extension-command-help.ts decide whether an extension flag consumes a value, and they disagree: extensionFlagTakesValueForInvocation (~L131) returns required OR value_name OR value_type!=boolean; formatDynamicExtensionParseOptionFlags (~L550) requires value_type!=boolean AND (value_name OR value_type OR required); buildDynamicExtensionHelpOptionSummary (~L650) sets takes_value/value_required from value_name alone, ignoring value_type. A flag declared with value_type=string but no value_name is a value flag to parse/recovery yet renders takes_value:false in help summaries; a required boolean diverges between the first two. Same drift family as CLOSED pm-9qcr (ext-contract boolean arity) and the pm-ulqu render-from-declared-domain class - fix by unifying on one contract-derived predicate, never per-surface patches."
